  "prompt": "How do I upload a picture to my little bitty picture window on Quora?",
  "response": "To upload a picture to your profile picture window (often referred to as your avatar) on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to Quora**: Open the Quora website or app and log in to your account.\n\n2. **Access Your Profile**: \n   - **On the Website**: Click on your current profile picture in the top right corner of the page, then select \"Profile\" from the dropdown menu.\n   - **On the App**: Tap on your profile picture in the bottom right corner, then select \"Profile.\"\n\n3. **Edit Your Profile**:\n   - **On the Website**: On your profile page, click the \"Edit\" button (it may look like a pencil icon or be labeled \"Edit Profile\").\n   - **On the App**: Tap the \"Edit Profile\" button.\n\n4. **Change Your Profile Picture**:\n   - **On the Website**: In the edit section, click on your current profile picture. A window will pop up allowing you to upload a new picture. You can choose a file from your computer.\n   - **On the App**: Tap on your current profile picture. You\u2019ll be prompted to either take a new photo or choose one from your device's photo library.\n\n5. **Adjust and Save**: After selecting the photo, you may have the option to crop or adjust it. Once you\u2019re satisfied, save the changes.\n\n6. **Confirm**: Your new profile picture should now be visible in your profile picture window on Quora.\n\nThat\u2019s it! Your picture is now updated and will be displayed on your Quora profile.",
